 :tx/rationale "STALE-SESSION-BUG-ANALYSIS: Session s-1773271079 from Session 021 was never closed, blocking auto-session-detection for 10+ sessions. Root cause: harvest does not close the active session — it writes harvest metadata but leaves session status unchanged. detect_session_start sees the old active session and returns false (session exists, skip). The fix was two-part: (1) manual transact to close the stale session, (2) add 2-hour staleness threshold to detect_session_start. But the deeper issue: the test suite verified the FUNCTION (detect_session_start works on a fresh store) but not the LIFECYCLE (session creates → work → harvest → session closes → next command → new session). Unit tests cover point-in-time state properties. Lifecycle properties (liveness: 'sessions eventually close') require temporal verification across multiple operations. This is the safety vs liveness gap: F(S) measures safety (nothing bad at this moment) but not liveness (something good eventually happens). TRACES TO: INV-HARVEST-007, INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-STORE-014."
